Package org.knime.core.webui.node.view.table.data.render

Class DataValueImageRendererRegistry

java.lang.Object
org.knime.core.webui.node.view.table.data.render.DataValueImageRendererRegistry
public final class DataValueImageRendererRegistry extends Object
Allows one to (short-term) register DataValueImageRenderers together with their respective DataValues to render. Required because the TableViewDataService doesn't return the rendered images directly but just a relative image path. The image is only rendered once the browser uses the provided path to render the image. And this class is intended to serve as the interchange between the place where the image path is returned via addRendererAndGetImgPath(String, DataCell, DataValueImageRenderer) (while iterating the data table) and the place where the image is finally rendered renderImage(String) (the data value is accessed again to finally render it for real).
Author:
Martin Horn, KNIME GmbH, Konstanz, Germany

  • Constructor Details

    • DataValueImageRendererRegistry

      public DataValueImageRendererRegistry(Supplier<String> pageIdSupplier)
      Parameters:
      pageIdSupplier - the page id of the view (see, e.g., PageResourceManager.getPageId(org.knime.core.webui.node.NodeWrapper)). It's used to define the relative path where image resources (output of the data value renderers) are available. Supplied lazily because the page id is not available yet on construction time of renderer factory. Can be null if no values are to be rendered into images.

      Returns:

    • renderImage

      public byte[] renderImage(String imgPath)
      Renders the image for the given relative image path and removes the respective renderer (and data value) from the registry.
      Parameters:
      imgPath - the relative image path. Can have optional 'w' and 'h' query parameters (e.g. ../img.png?w=10&h=10) which define the maximal width and height the image is to be scaled down to (the returned image will never be scaled up, though). If not given, it will be returned in its original size.
      Returns:
      the image data or an empty array if the image data can't be accessed (anymore)

    • getImageDimensions

      public DataValueImageRenderer.ImageDimension getImageDimensions(String imgPath)
      Retrieves the image dimensions for the given image path
      Parameters:
      imgPath - the relative image path without height and width information (see addRendererAndGetImgPath(String tableId, DataCell cell, DataValueImageRenderer renderer))
      Returns:
      the image dimensions or null when the images cannot be accessed anymore

    • startNewBatchOfTableRows

      public void startNewBatchOfTableRows(String tableId)
      Signals that a new batch of table row is being requested. By that, this registry knows to what batch of rows certain images belong which latter helps to partially clear the cache (e.g. only removing images from the oldest batch).
      Parameters:
      tableId - the table to start the new batch for
